# The Fell God's Flame · the fire that burns the Erdtree

The Fell God is the Outer God of the Fire Giants, and its flame is the one fire that can burn the Erdtree. That single fact sets it apart from every other fire: not the brightest, not the holiest, but the only one the Erdtree cannot survive.

Marika's war crushed the giants — and then did something stranger than extinguish their god's fire. She cursed the last survivor of their kind to tend the Flame of Ruin forever atop the Mountaintops, and set the Fire Monks to watch that it never wakes. The destroying flame was not destroyed. It was chained, kept burning under guard, waiting in the Forge of the Giants.

And the chain matters, because the world's path runs back to it. To walk the path of the game's ending, the Tarnished must set this very fire to the Erdtree's base — the forbidden flame becoming the necessary one.

Its emergence is natural: this is fire-as-fire, no metaphor required. It burns, embodied in a forge, a mountaintop, and a cursed keeper — chained but never extinguished, waiting to do the one thing only it can do.
